    <shortlink>ux list csevent listreadytopersist</shortlink>
    <topic>listReadyToPersist</topic>
    <description>Fires when the list is ready to persist to storage.</description>
    <arguments>
        <argument>
            <name>listSyncMode</name>
            <type>string</type>
            <description>
                <p>The synchronization mode used. Can be one of the following:</p>
                <p>
                    <list bullet="true">
                        <item>
                            <name>fullRefresh</name>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <name>incrementalRefresh</name>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <name>listSyncNoMediaFiles</name>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <name>listSyncMediaFiles</name>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </description>
        </argument>
    </arguments>
    <discussion>
        <p>The *[js:listReadyToPersist]* event is triggered when the List is ready to be persisted to local storage or the device file system.</p>
        <p>This event is only reliable if the List has a Detail View and has fields configured to download media files.</p>
    </discussion>

    <see>
        <ref link="ux%20list%20events">List Control Client-side Events</ref>
        <ref link="ux%20list%20csevent">Detail View Client-side Events</ref>
        <ref link="ux%20list%20builder%20jsruntime%20properties">Javascript - Run Time</ref>
        <ref link="ux%20list%20builder%20jsrendertime%20properties">Javascript - Render Time</ref>
    </see>
